I've tried it both via cable and wifi adb and worked with no problem.

@stasfilin i was able to debug the problem, and it appears that problem is in aiohttp (cc @asvetlov).

Here's where [problem appears ](https://github.com/KeepSafe/aiohttp/blob/master/aiohttp/web_urldispatcher.py#L99-L121). The explanation is quite trivial, when coroutine is being decorated by regular function (which is not a coroutine), aiohttp just reassigns wrapper without pulling out required fields of decorated coroutine. So, [wrapper_handler](https://github.com/KeepSafe/aiohttp/blob/master/aiohttp/web_urldispatcher.py#L110) `__doc__` is obviously equals to `None`. And that's why aiohttp_swagger is not capable to pull out docstrings from route handlers.

In my own case, i would need to rewrite decorator to be a coroutine, but not a regular function.

