It appears that the issue is triggered when the backend responds to a track lookup with an embedded album object that does not include a `uri` property. It's not clear to me from the Mopidy API documentation whether `uri` can be expected to be present and non-empty. But even if the backend is returning an incomplete object, i.e. a backend bug, should it also be the responsibility of the UI to not make a malformed request such as `"params": ["undefined"]` if the `uri` property is missing?

