@richard-bosworth tappy currently has no ability to *produce* YAML blocks. The latest version that I pushed out added the ability to *consume* YAML blocks via the parser API.

Since the output for tappy is currently version 12 format, I intentionally left off `TAP version 13` to be maximally compatible with other consumers.

I'm happy to consider adding TAP version 13, but I'm not sure that I see the advantage or need at the moment. We can use this issue to weight the pros/cons and see if adding the version 13 identifier makes sense.

Yes, I think it's strange that throughput degrades as buffer size increases. In some experiments I ran, bigger object sizes triggered the "double transmission" bug (a retry was triggered). This **may** be why we're seeing slower times for larger buffer sizes.

